# Copy to .env at the repo root and fill in ONE of the two modes below.
# NEVER commit .env. Treat any value below like a password — rotate
# immediately if exposed (chat, screenshots, git history, etc.).

# =============================================================================
# MODE 1 (recommended): Vertex AI — bills against your Vertex / general
#                       Google Cloud credits.
# =============================================================================
# 1. Set the project (and optionally location; default us-central1):
# GOOGLE_CLOUD_PROJECT=project-v1
# GOOGLE_CLOUD_LOCATION=us-central1
#
# 2. Authenticate once on your machine (outside this file):
#      gcloud auth application-default login
#      gcloud auth application-default set-quota-project project-v1
#      gcloud services enable aiplatform.googleapis.com --project=project-v1
#
# No key value goes in this file for Vertex mode — ADC handles auth.

# =============================================================================
# MODE 2 (fallback): Gemini Developer API key — SEPARATE billing SKU from
#                    Vertex AI. Your Vertex credits do NOT apply here.
# =============================================================================
# Get a key at https://aistudio.google.com/apikey OR in Cloud Console >
# APIs & Services > Credentials. If you see 429 "prepayment credits
# depleted", either enable billing for the Generative Language API on your
# Cloud project, or switch to Mode 1 above.
#
# GEMINI_API_KEY=your-gemini-api-key-here
